Item 8.01 Other Events
     On February 28, 2005, the Registrant publicly disseminated a press release announcing a voluntary suspension in the marketing and commercial distribution of TYSABRI (natalizumab), a treatment for multiple sclerosis, and that physicians should suspend dosing of TYSABRI until further notification. The press release also announced that dosing of TYSABRI would be suspended in all clinical trials. The information contained in the press release is incorporated herein by reference and filed as Exhibit 99.1 hereto.
Item 9.01 Financial Statements and Exhibits
